  "original_title": "\u0d91\u0dc5\u0dc0\u0dc5\u0dd4 \u0db4\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dc0\u0dcf\u0dc4\u0db1 \u0dbd\u0ddc\u0dbb\u0dd2 \u0dc0\u0dbd\u0da7 \u0dc4\u0db8\u0dd4\u0daf\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0da9\u0dd3\u0dc3\u0dbd\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Army diesel for vegetable transport trucks",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Nuwara Eliya District Secretary Nandana Galaboda said that the Sri Lanka 3rd Lions Regiment (SLAF) in Nuwara Eliya has started issuing diesel fuel to lorries transporting vegetables daily from the Nuwara Eliya Economic Center to the Colombo Manning Market and other economic centers in the province on the 1st of this month.",
        "According to this, the officials of the Nuwara Eliya Economic Center gave a list of the lorries that are running daily, and steps were taken to release fuel from the army camp to those lorries and to the lorries that bring the harvest of vegetable farmers in the Nuwara Eliya area to the Nuwara Eliya Economic Center on a daily basis. The district secretary said.",
        "Farmers growing vegetables in Nuwara Eliya were in dire straits as they were unable to send their crops to the market due to the lack of diesel fuel."
      ],
